shared_text:
Village of Lisle ‚Äì Government
August 18 at 9:29 AM ¬∑

Carlin ‚ÄúCoach‚Äù Nalley Receives Honorary Street Designation

At a Lisle Village Board meeting held August 17th, Mayor Christopher Pecak proclaimed Saturday, September 12, 2020 as Carlin ‚ÄúCoach‚Äù Nalley Day in the Village of Lisle. In addition to the proclamation, School Street, between Main Street and Spencer Avenue, has been designated to receive an honorary street designation in recognition of Coach Nalley‚Äôs contributions. The nomination for the honorary street designation was submitted by the Carlin Nalley Foundation.

Carlin Nalley served Lisle CUSD 202 for 30 years in the classroom, athletic arenas, district leadership, and as a community leader. He was also the first Director of the Lisle Park District where he established park programs utilizing a symbiotic relationship between school and park districts, which helped launch park programs for all community members and made efficient use of public resources. Carlin ‚ÄúCoach‚Äù Nalley continues to serve as an IHSA track and field official for many events in the area and assists in some of the current local programs.

Calling all parents!
3 quick things...üëá
1. Please make sure you complete your registration in PowerSchool for the school year. You must register for school whether you select In-Person or online learning. https://lislecusd202.powerschool.com/public/home.html

2. When you are completing your registration in PowerSchool, you need to click on "Forms" to upload your proofs of residency. Your registration is not complete without this step.

3. In addition to PowerSchool registration, all parents need to complete the Attendance Selection Form to indicate how your child will participate in school this year - In-Person or online. The information and form can be found at https://www.lisle202.org/return-to-school

FYI~
The DuPage County community-based COVID-19 testing site will be closed for the federal holiday on Friday, July 3rd and Saturday, July 4th. Normal operating hours will resume on Tuesday, July 7th.

DuPage County is offering community-based COVID-19 testing at the DuPage County Complex. The entrance is located on County Farm Road a few blocks North of Roosevelt Road at a stoplight. Follow the signs through the campus to the test site.

Testing is free but limited tests are available per day. This is a drive-thru testing site where individuals will give themselves a nasal swab test with instructions from staff.

Hours of Operation
7:00 a.m. - 3:00 p.m. Tuesday - Saturday
(all cars must arrive by 2 p.m. to be tested and site may close earlier if daily test capacity is met)

Caps off to you, Lisle Graduate!

Irene Panos Evert‚ÄéLisle Junior High Home and School Organization
May 14 at 7:58 PM ¬∑

UPDATE: Shane‚Äôs has asked us to reach out to families and let them know that they should order before the June 15th deadline to ensure they get their order. If your school does not resume in the fall we will still make our anticipated delivery of your school kits.

UPDATE: Home Delivery -Due to the challenges with social distancing and guidance from our governor, we are going to have less staff this year, affecting our school kit production. In order to ensure that we have the time to produce all of the school kits that are ordered this season and have them ready in time for school we will be CLOSING our home delivery ordering site on JULY 15th.

Order your School Supplies NOW! No need to shop the lines or go all over town.
Your kits have been teacher approved for your students classes!
Order your kit before JUNE 15TH for FREE Shipping to the school.
Convenient Home delivery is available June 16 - July 15th for a delivery fee, one fee per household, not per order.
charge per household, not per kit.

post_text:
IDHS Announces Call4Calm

The Illinois Department of Human Services has launched a support line called Call4Calm that is reachable via text. Individuals who want to speak with a mental health professional can text the word ‚ÄúTALK‚Äù or ‚ÄúHABLAR‚Äù (for Spanish speakers) to 552-020. That individual will receive a call from a mental health professional employed by a local community health center. People can also text other terms, like ‚Äúunemployment‚Äù or ‚Äúfood‚Äù or ‚Äúshelter‚Äù to the same number to receive information on how to navigate and access supports and services. Call4Calm is free, and individuals who use it can remain anonymous.
text:
IDHS Announces Call4Calm

The Illinois Department of Human Services has launched a support line called Call4Calm that is reachable via text. Individuals who want to speak with a mental health professional can text the word ‚ÄúTALK‚Äù or ‚ÄúHABLAR‚Äù (for Spanish speakers) to 552-020. That individual will receive a call from a mental health professional employed by a local community health center. People can also text other terms, like ‚Äúunemployment‚Äù or ‚Äúfood‚Äù or ‚Äúshelter‚Äù to the same number to receive information on how to navigate and access supports and services. Call4Calm is free, and individuals who use it can remain anonymous.

Community Notification Enrollment

Lisle Police Department
March 25 at 5:26 PM ¬∑

We utilize a community notification service called Code Red. This allows us to send residents emergency information via emails, text messages, or phone calls.

If you are already signed up, you may want to add the below telephone numbers into your telephone's contacts so that you recognize the CodeRED system on your caller ID when you get a call. The numbers are as follows:
866-419-5000 for Emergency Alerts & Notifications,
855-969-4636 for General Notifications,
800-566-9780 for Weather Alerts.

If you are not signed up for these alerts, please visit https://tinyurl.com/CodeRedLisle or Text the word Lisle to 99411 to sign up.

Although we anticipate the Illinois Governor to make a similar announcement in the near future, we have not received any information on the closure extending beyond March 30th at this time. We are in regular contact with local, state, and federal leaders and will share additional information as it becomes available.

Please be assured our top priority is the health and safety of our entire learning community and we appreciate your patience as we navigate through these unprecedented times together.

post_text:
SCHOOL CLOSURE FOOD SERVICE BEGINS TODAY
During the mandatory school closing, Lisle 202 will provide a free meal for any student, 18 years and younger, or who is enrolled in school. The meals will be a cold, grab-n-go lunch and will most likely consist of a sandwich, fruit or vegetable, and milk.

Meals will be available for pick-up:
Days/Dates: Monday-Friday, beginning Tuesday, March 17th through Friday, April 3rd
Where: Lisle Senior High School, 1800 Short Street, Lisle, IL
Times: 11am-1pm

Please pull up at the curb in front of the main entrance and the food will be brought to your car. There is no need to exit your car.

This opportunity is open to ALL children in the District 202 boundaries. One lunch per student will be provided on the first day of the program. The frequency of pick-up will be addressed after the first day based on the number of families that choose to participate.

If you have questions or need assistance regarding this meals program, please contact the District Office at 630-493-8000.

February 1 at 10:10 AM ¬∑

Hello 8th Grade Parents!
We are looking for volunteers to share ideas and help plan the 8th Grade Graduation Celebration.

What is the 8th grade celebration?
After the graduation ceremony on May 20th the students are treated to a celebration at the Junior High. This is attended by the students, staff and a few parent volunteers. Food, dancing and treats are provided for one last Junior High night of fun and lasting memories!

If you are interested in sharing ideas or volunteering, please join us for our first planning meeting on Tuesday February 4th after taking your family to our restaurant night at Taco Dale!

Where: Lisle Junior High Conference Room at 7:15.

Please let Rebecca Harris or Mary Ebert know if you want to join the committee. Hope to see you Tuesday!
